1
00:00:09,708 --> 00:00:10,541
[bullet ricochets]

2
00:00:13,250 --> 00:00:14,625
[gasping]

3
00:00:14,708 --> 00:00:16,458
Marlya. Hang on.

4
00:00:16,541 --> 00:00:17,958
Explain yourself.

5
00:00:18,041 --> 00:00:19,500
What the hell did you do?

6
00:00:19,583 --> 00:00:23,333
♪

7
00:00:32,250 --> 00:00:33,875
[roaring]

8
00:00:37,166 --> 00:00:39,125
[grunts, sighs]

9
00:00:40,708 --> 00:00:42,500
[snarls]

10
00:00:42,583 --> 00:00:44,541
[sighs]

11
00:00:45,958 --> 00:00:47,250
[FREE]
Now I get it.

12
00:00:47,333 --> 00:00:50,291
Whatever damage we do,
is inflicted back on us.

13
00:00:53,291 --> 00:00:55,166
-[growling]
-[SWEETIE chuckles]

14
00:00:55,250 --> 00:00:58,458
[SWEETIE] Well done, Skriker.
Good fairy.

15
00:01:00,458 --> 00:01:02,500
[FREE] She was trouble
enough by herself,

16
00:01:02,583 --> 00:01:05,583
but now I’ve also got to contend
with that bizarre fairy.

17
00:01:07,125 --> 00:01:08,708
-[BOTH grunting]
-[metal scraping]

18
00:01:08,791 --> 00:01:10,666
[snarling]

19
00:01:10,750 --> 00:01:12,583
-[grunting]
-[FREE gasps]

20
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:16,458
[gunfire]

21
00:01:18,333 --> 00:01:21,333
Oh wow.
Is that some new popular dance?

22
00:01:21,416 --> 00:01:23,291
-I hate you.
-[SWEETIE] Why’d you stop?

23
00:01:23,375 --> 00:01:24,583
Please, continue.

24
00:01:24,666 --> 00:01:26,833
Only if you’d care to join,
Sweetie.

25
00:01:26,916 --> 00:01:28,041
[SWEETIE chuckles]

26
00:01:28,125 --> 00:01:30,083
[MARLYA]
Ow.

27
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,750
The dust must cause the damage.

28
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:36,041
It’s everywhere.

29
00:01:37,375 --> 00:01:39,208
[FAIRIES growling]

30
00:01:39,291 --> 00:01:41,875
Are you sure
you still want to play?

31
00:01:41,958 --> 00:01:45,000
If you’re not in the mood,
I can take this off your hands.

32
00:01:45,083 --> 00:01:47,333
[MARLYA] I won’t let you steal
the Black Fairy Tome!

33
00:01:50,500 --> 00:01:52,041
[gasps]

34
00:01:54,333 --> 00:01:56,166
You fool!
I was going to spare you!

35
00:01:56,250 --> 00:01:57,750
[SKRIKER snarls]

36
00:01:59,750 --> 00:02:01,208
Fall back, Marlya!

37
00:02:02,791 --> 00:02:05,458
-[SWEETIE groaning]
-[SKRIKER growling]

38
00:02:05,541 --> 00:02:07,291
You will not outlast me!

39
00:02:14,250 --> 00:02:15,791
I must say,
that look suits you.

40
00:02:15,875 --> 00:02:17,333
Being protected by a girl.

41
00:02:17,416 --> 00:02:18,333
Oh, shut up!

42
00:02:18,416 --> 00:02:20,291
You’ll regret this, I swear!

43
00:02:20,375 --> 00:02:22,625
We showed her, didn’t we, Free?

44
00:02:22,708 --> 00:02:24,916
The Black Fairy Tome’s ours.

45
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:27,125
Yeah, thanks to you.

46
00:02:30,708 --> 00:02:31,750
[MARLYA winces]

47
00:02:33,125 --> 00:02:34,875
Easy there.
You’re hurt.

48
00:02:36,625 --> 00:02:39,208
Not bad, huh, Partner?

49
00:02:40,750 --> 00:02:42,458
You did good, kid.

50
00:02:42,541 --> 00:02:43,833
[MARLYA chuckles]

51
00:02:45,125 --> 00:02:46,333
[sighs]

52
00:04:27,208 --> 00:04:28,166
[RAY]
Burn it all!

53
00:04:28,250 --> 00:04:29,541
[MAN] Why? Ray Dawn?

54
00:04:29,625 --> 00:04:31,083
Why’re you doing this?

55
00:04:32,375 --> 00:04:34,333
[BOTH panting]

56
00:04:36,208 --> 00:04:37,500
[SOLDIER A]
They must’ve gone this way!

57
00:04:37,583 --> 00:04:38,958
[SOLDIER B]
Don’t let them escape!

58
00:04:39,041 --> 00:04:41,208
[SOLDIER C]
Burn the entire forest!

59
00:04:41,291 --> 00:04:44,291
[YOUNG MARLYA crying]

60
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:50,166
I’ll draw the soldiers
in the other direction.

61
00:04:50,250 --> 00:04:51,583
Use that time to escape.

62
00:04:51,666 --> 00:04:54,500
[YOUNG MARLYA]
But if you do that, you’ll be...

63
00:04:54,583 --> 00:04:56,875
Don’t worry.
You know how fast I am.

64
00:04:56,958 --> 00:04:59,291
They’ll never be
able to catch up.

65
00:04:59,375 --> 00:05:00,750
I’ll be alright.

66
00:05:00,833 --> 00:05:03,333
Stay here.
Don’t go, Ver.

67
00:05:04,416 --> 00:05:06,500
Ver!

68
00:05:12,291 --> 00:05:15,041
[YOUNG VERONICA]
It’s okay. Trust me.

69
00:05:15,125 --> 00:05:17,583
I won’t let
anything bad happen.

70
00:05:17,666 --> 00:05:20,125
[birds chirping]

71
00:05:20,208 --> 00:05:22,625
♪

72
00:05:28,166 --> 00:05:29,666
[gasps softly]

73
00:05:33,250 --> 00:05:36,125
[ethereal whispering]

74
00:05:36,208 --> 00:05:38,750
So many fairies.

75
00:05:40,458 --> 00:05:41,458
[inhales sharply]

76
00:05:43,791 --> 00:05:46,041
Shh.

77
00:05:47,750 --> 00:05:50,041
[YOUNG VERONICA]
Your name’s Marlya, isn’t it?

78
00:05:50,125 --> 00:05:52,250
[YOUNG MARLYA]
If you knew that, then why...

79
00:05:52,333 --> 00:05:54,041
[YOUNG VERONICA]
Why what?

80
00:05:54,125 --> 00:05:56,583
[YOUNG MARLYA]
I mean. I’m just...

81
00:05:56,666 --> 00:05:59,250
♪

82
00:05:59,333 --> 00:06:02,375
[YOUNG VERONICA]
It’s okay. You can trust me.

83
00:06:02,458 --> 00:06:04,583
I won’t let anything bad happen.

84
00:06:04,666 --> 00:06:06,791
♪

85
00:06:19,875 --> 00:06:21,583
Don’t go.

86
00:06:30,041 --> 00:06:32,000
This isn’t Sweetie’s blood.

87
00:06:32,083 --> 00:06:33,541
Axel’s then?

88
00:06:34,708 --> 00:06:37,416
Did someone carry him
out of here?

89
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:39,333
[birds shrieking]

90
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:42,000
[knock on door]

91
00:06:47,333 --> 00:06:49,750
Did you have any luck
with the investigation?

92
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:52,000
I managed to uncover
a few clues.

93
00:06:52,083 --> 00:06:54,916
The party responsible
might’ve escaped,

94
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,541
but at least we were able
to recover the Black Fairy Tome.

95
00:06:58,625 --> 00:07:01,291
Speaking of which,
your colleague is still asleep.

96
00:07:01,375 --> 00:07:02,833
[FREE]
I expected as much.

97
00:07:02,916 --> 00:07:04,750
Thank you for
letting her rest here.

98
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:06,208
Think nothing of it.

99
00:07:06,291 --> 00:07:07,833
Having Dorothea in my debt

100
00:07:07,916 --> 00:07:09,750
could prove
extremely useful later on.

101
00:07:09,833 --> 00:07:12,125
[laughs softly]
Would it be okay

102
00:07:12,208 --> 00:07:13,958
if we remained your guests
until she wakes up?

103
00:07:14,041 --> 00:07:15,125
Certainly.

104
00:07:15,208 --> 00:07:16,833
Stay as long as you need.

105
00:07:18,250 --> 00:07:20,875
♪

106
00:07:27,791 --> 00:07:29,333
[DIESE]
Does that bring this inspection

107
00:07:29,416 --> 00:07:31,291
to a close, Nein Auler?

108
00:07:31,375 --> 00:07:33,416
[NEIN]
Yes. Thank you, Duke Hybranz.

109
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:35,750
Why so formal?
You and I go way back.

110
00:07:35,833 --> 00:07:37,541
It’s Schwarz Diese, please.

111
00:07:37,625 --> 00:07:39,125
[NEIN]
The war is over,

112
00:07:39,208 --> 00:07:41,958
and while I may not be
your subordinate any longer,

113
00:07:42,041 --> 00:07:45,208
I’m afraid I’m in no position
to be informal.

114
00:07:45,291 --> 00:07:46,625
[DIESE]
Hmm.

115
00:07:46,708 --> 00:07:48,583
I assure you,
there’s nothing here

116
00:07:48,666 --> 00:07:51,083
I wouldn’t want
your people to see.

117
00:07:53,625 --> 00:07:55,666
I hope I’ve made
that crystal clear.

118
00:07:55,750 --> 00:07:58,625
The government will receive
my full report.

119
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:04,625
[DIESE]
Hmm.

120
00:08:04,708 --> 00:08:06,958
If I break the law,
I don’t leave evidence.

121
00:08:07,041 --> 00:08:09,375
The same is true
if I choose to obey it.

122
00:08:09,458 --> 00:08:11,625
You’re aware
how pointless this is.

123
00:08:11,708 --> 00:08:14,833
Regardless, sir,
we simply carry out our duty.

124
00:08:14,916 --> 00:08:17,166
[DIESE exhales sharply]
You weren’t kidding.

125
00:08:17,250 --> 00:08:18,875
You haven’t changed.

126
00:08:18,958 --> 00:08:21,250
[NEIN]
Thank you for your cooperation.

127
00:08:21,333 --> 00:08:22,666
We’ll be taking our leave.

128
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:23,833
[DIESE]
Of course.

129
00:08:23,916 --> 00:08:25,916
I hope I was
able to be of service.

130
00:08:28,666 --> 00:08:31,583
-[grunting]
-[heavy wheels moving]

131
00:08:38,041 --> 00:08:38,875
[PATTY sighs]

132
00:08:40,333 --> 00:08:42,333
Made it! How are ya?

133
00:08:47,208 --> 00:08:48,541
[WAITER]
Can I take your order?

134
00:08:48,625 --> 00:08:50,583
Sure. One fresh water.

135
00:08:50,666 --> 00:08:52,375
You only want water, miss?

136
00:08:52,458 --> 00:08:54,375
Fresh water, you stooge.

137
00:08:54,458 --> 00:08:56,166
[WAITER]
Coming right up.

138
00:08:56,250 --> 00:08:58,166
If he brings me a glass
and it’s stale,

139
00:08:58,250 --> 00:09:00,041
-he’s a dead man.
-[SWEETIE] I’m glad to see

140
00:09:00,125 --> 00:09:01,541
you haven’t changed
one bit, Patricia.

141
00:09:01,625 --> 00:09:03,000
[SWEETIE laughs softly]

142
00:09:03,083 --> 00:09:05,250
It’s Patty.
Sweets.

143
00:09:05,333 --> 00:09:08,541
What incredible luck
you were in Isharat already.

144
00:09:08,625 --> 00:09:12,000
And here I was thinking
I would have to send for you.

145
00:09:12,083 --> 00:09:13,125
Jonathan.

146
00:09:13,208 --> 00:09:14,875
Is he in the city too?

147
00:09:14,958 --> 00:09:16,166
He’s around.

148
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:17,875
So what did you have in mind?

149
00:09:19,958 --> 00:09:21,708
Your specialty.

150
00:09:21,791 --> 00:09:23,500
Tying up loose ends.

151
00:09:27,833 --> 00:09:29,458
[moaning]

152
00:09:29,541 --> 00:09:30,416
[gasps sharply]

153
00:09:31,583 --> 00:09:33,875
Why do I feel so drained?

154
00:09:36,166 --> 00:09:38,041
You’re here.

155
00:09:38,125 --> 00:09:41,791
[groans]

156
00:09:41,875 --> 00:09:43,541
Finally woke up.

157
00:09:43,625 --> 00:09:45,208
Guess so,

158
00:09:45,291 --> 00:09:46,916
but how long
was I out for?

159
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:48,166
[FREE]
A while.

160
00:09:48,250 --> 00:09:51,208
-Almost an entire day.
-That long, huh?

161
00:09:51,291 --> 00:09:53,750
Things could have been a lot
worse than how they turned out.

162
00:09:53,833 --> 00:09:55,666
Don’t push yourself too hard.

163
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:58,000
I’ll try not to, doctor.

164
00:09:59,750 --> 00:10:01,458
You can sit up?

165
00:10:01,541 --> 00:10:03,416
Yes. It’s just.

166
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:05,250
Where’s the Black Fairy Tome?

167
00:10:06,875 --> 00:10:08,791
[chuckles] You mean this?

168
00:10:08,875 --> 00:10:10,250
[MARLYA gasps softly]

169
00:10:10,333 --> 00:10:11,833
[FREE]
You’ll receive the credit.

170
00:10:13,833 --> 00:10:15,000
But it’s all for nothing

171
00:10:15,083 --> 00:10:16,916
if the Tome proves
to be a counterfeit.

172
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,875
You mean it isn’t
the real thing?

173
00:10:18,958 --> 00:10:20,958
I’ll have to deliver it
to the Ministry of Fairies

174
00:10:21,041 --> 00:10:22,375
for appraisal first.

175
00:10:22,458 --> 00:10:23,583
We’ll know after that.

176
00:10:23,666 --> 00:10:25,291
Out of all the texts,

177
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:27,833
the Black Tome
is by far the most valuable.

178
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:31,125
It’s not uncommon for forgeries
to be bought and sold.

179
00:10:33,041 --> 00:10:33,875
[MARLYA groans]

180
00:10:34,875 --> 00:10:38,125
-Like at mafia auctions.
-[FREE] Yeah.

181
00:10:38,208 --> 00:10:40,791
They become the showpiece
whenever they’re featured.

182
00:10:40,875 --> 00:10:42,500
Like the one we were guarding.

183
00:10:42,583 --> 00:10:44,125
Seems it’s necessary.

184
00:10:44,208 --> 00:10:45,750
There’s been trouble
at a number of auctions

185
00:10:45,833 --> 00:10:47,083
these last few years.

186
00:10:47,166 --> 00:10:49,208
[MARLYA]
Yeah, I heard something similar.

187
00:10:49,291 --> 00:10:51,625
I didn’t hear of any robberies
at Gui Carlin

188
00:10:51,708 --> 00:10:53,208
gatherings up to that point.

189
00:10:53,291 --> 00:10:55,708
We didn’t have any detailed
information either.

190
00:10:57,583 --> 00:10:58,625
Your friend.

191
00:10:58,708 --> 00:10:59,958
You thought she was the one

192
00:11:00,041 --> 00:11:01,666
hitting the auctions.

193
00:11:01,750 --> 00:11:03,333
[MARLYA]
I didn’t have any proof,

194
00:11:03,416 --> 00:11:05,500
but that’s what I figured.

195
00:11:05,583 --> 00:11:08,083
There were some connections.

196
00:11:08,166 --> 00:11:10,208
[FREE]
To the mafia, you mean?

197
00:11:10,291 --> 00:11:11,875
[MARLYA]
Then she showed up,

198
00:11:11,958 --> 00:11:14,166
and came for the
Black Fairy Tome.

199
00:11:14,250 --> 00:11:15,875
Then took off with it.

200
00:11:15,958 --> 00:11:17,000
[FREE sighs]

201
00:11:17,083 --> 00:11:18,291
[FREE]
Who knows.

202
00:11:18,375 --> 00:11:20,333
Maybe that’s
how this made it

203
00:11:20,416 --> 00:11:21,958
all the way to Isharat.

204
00:11:22,041 --> 00:11:23,458
And if that’s true,

205
00:11:23,541 --> 00:11:26,083
then Cain and Damien
might know about her.

206
00:11:43,666 --> 00:11:45,625
You want to know
how we got our hands

207
00:11:45,708 --> 00:11:47,166
on the Black Fairy Tome.

208
00:11:47,250 --> 00:11:50,500
No surprise, but...

209
00:11:52,125 --> 00:11:53,333
[DAMIEN]
My apologies.

210
00:11:53,416 --> 00:11:55,291
That’s something
we cannot reveal.

211
00:11:55,375 --> 00:11:57,333
You can’t or you won’t?

212
00:11:57,416 --> 00:11:59,250
[CAIN sighs]

213
00:11:59,333 --> 00:12:01,833
Is this an official inquiry
from Dorothea?

214
00:12:01,916 --> 00:12:03,041
[chuckling]
Not at all.

215
00:12:03,125 --> 00:12:04,416
Our business is concluded.

216
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:05,625
You reported to the Ministry

217
00:12:05,708 --> 00:12:06,875
that you had
the Black Fairy Tome

218
00:12:06,958 --> 00:12:09,000
in your possession
and so they sent us.

219
00:12:09,083 --> 00:12:11,791
Our only interest was
retrieving the text from you.

220
00:12:11,875 --> 00:12:13,375
Then this
is a simple chat.

221
00:12:13,458 --> 00:12:15,666
Since it isn’t government
business, I’ll say this.

222
00:12:15,750 --> 00:12:17,208
There are things
we can reveal to you

223
00:12:17,291 --> 00:12:19,166
and things we cannot.

224
00:12:19,250 --> 00:12:20,750
Look at it this way.

225
00:12:20,833 --> 00:12:22,208
We have to protect our sources.

226
00:12:22,291 --> 00:12:24,375
Private Fairy scholars like us

227
00:12:24,458 --> 00:12:25,791
are barely allowed to exist

228
00:12:25,875 --> 00:12:27,583
since we share the results
of our research

229
00:12:27,666 --> 00:12:28,958
with Unified Zesskia.

230
00:12:29,041 --> 00:12:30,333
But after the war,

231
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:31,833
I seem to recall
the Ministry

232
00:12:31,916 --> 00:12:33,458
offering jobs
to people in your field.

233
00:12:33,541 --> 00:12:36,208
I was too low on the ladder
for them to even notice me.

234
00:12:36,291 --> 00:12:39,625
Cain on the other hand received
multiple invitations to join.

235
00:12:39,708 --> 00:12:42,833
By the time the war ended,
I was already an old man.

236
00:12:42,916 --> 00:12:46,166
I wanted to spend my remaining
years free of bureaucracy.

237
00:12:47,875 --> 00:12:49,166
Well, In that case,

238
00:12:49,250 --> 00:12:50,833
could you
tell me just one thing?

239
00:12:52,083 --> 00:12:53,375
Veronica Thorn.

240
00:12:53,458 --> 00:12:55,041
Have you heard that name before?

241
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:58,791
Regrettably,
it’s not ringing a bell.

242
00:12:58,875 --> 00:13:01,125
-Damien. You?
-No.

243
00:13:01,208 --> 00:13:03,291
I’ve not. Sorry.

244
00:13:04,416 --> 00:13:05,708
[MARLYA]
I see.

245
00:13:05,791 --> 00:13:07,875
If you’ll excuse me.

246
00:13:07,958 --> 00:13:10,583
♪

247
00:13:25,708 --> 00:13:28,583
[birds squawking]

248
00:13:35,916 --> 00:13:38,083
-[bell ringing]
-[indistinct chatter]

249
00:13:42,250 --> 00:13:44,666
[voracious chewing]

250
00:13:48,416 --> 00:13:50,250
[FREE]
You don’t need to wolf it down.

251
00:13:50,333 --> 00:13:51,625
We have plenty of time.

252
00:13:51,708 --> 00:13:53,666
Our train isn’t leaving
for a while.

253
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:56,583
How am I supposed to get better
if I don’t eat?

254
00:13:56,666 --> 00:13:59,083
Also, I wasn’t wolfing.

255
00:13:59,166 --> 00:14:00,500
[FREE sighs]

256
00:14:03,958 --> 00:14:05,250
Hey, not half bad.

257
00:14:05,333 --> 00:14:07,333
-[MARLYA] Those people.
-Huh?

258
00:14:07,416 --> 00:14:10,583
I’m going to assume you’re
referring to Cain and Damien.

259
00:14:10,666 --> 00:14:12,083
-Yeah.
-Ah.

260
00:14:12,166 --> 00:14:14,875
I know I should be grateful
they let me stay there,

261
00:14:14,958 --> 00:14:16,250
but they’re liars.

262
00:14:16,333 --> 00:14:17,875
That’s quite the accusation.

263
00:14:17,958 --> 00:14:20,458
-You got any proof?
-No, but you!

264
00:14:20,541 --> 00:14:22,500
[FREE] Can’t blame them
for concealing their sources.

265
00:14:22,583 --> 00:14:23,916
[MARLYA groans]

266
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:26,583
How else can they survive?
Like they said,

267
00:14:26,666 --> 00:14:29,458
being a private
fairy scholar is tough, so...

268
00:14:29,541 --> 00:14:30,708
[MARLYA]
Then maybe they should join

269
00:14:30,791 --> 00:14:32,416
the Ministry of Fairies
or whatever.

270
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:33,833
And stop complaining.

271
00:14:33,916 --> 00:14:35,125
They don’t want to.

272
00:14:35,208 --> 00:14:36,666
Once the chain’s
around their neck,

273
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:38,166
there are things
they can’t do.

274
00:14:38,250 --> 00:14:39,666
[PATTY]
Am I glad to put this down!

275
00:14:39,750 --> 00:14:40,750
[BOTH] Huh?

276
00:14:40,833 --> 00:14:44,000
Please, don’t pay me any mind.

277
00:14:49,291 --> 00:14:50,708
[WAITER]
What’ll it be?

278
00:14:50,791 --> 00:14:53,458
[PATTY] I’ll have a glass
of fresh water.

279
00:14:53,541 --> 00:14:55,500
Water. That’s it?

280
00:14:55,583 --> 00:14:57,541
[PATTY]
And make sure it’s fresh.

281
00:14:57,625 --> 00:15:00,041
-Of course, madame.
-As for me,

282
00:15:00,125 --> 00:15:02,208
I’ll have love and despair,
back and forth.

283
00:15:02,291 --> 00:15:05,500
-Served at their most extreme.
-[WAITER] Sir?

284
00:15:05,583 --> 00:15:07,041
[PATTY] Just bring him
something off the menu

285
00:15:07,125 --> 00:15:08,625
that doesn’t take
long to prepare.

286
00:15:08,708 --> 00:15:10,291
[WAITER]
Right away.

287
00:15:12,958 --> 00:15:14,375
Hi.

288
00:15:14,458 --> 00:15:15,833
[FREE]
Uh...

289
00:15:15,916 --> 00:15:17,333
[FREE chuckles]

290
00:15:17,416 --> 00:15:18,583
[MARLYA groans]

291
00:15:22,750 --> 00:15:24,125
[MARLYA]
Where did...?

292
00:15:24,208 --> 00:15:25,583
-[PATTY chuckles]
-[FREE] Huh?

293
00:15:27,833 --> 00:15:30,416
[PATTY groans, chuckles]

294
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:32,625
I’ll be seeing you around.

295
00:15:32,708 --> 00:15:36,500
She left? What about her water?

296
00:15:36,583 --> 00:15:38,000
-[FREE grunts]
-[MARLYA gasps]

297
00:15:38,083 --> 00:15:39,916
[MARLYA]
What is it?

298
00:15:41,750 --> 00:15:43,416
-Ta-ta.
-Hey, stop!

299
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:44,958
Wait, where are you going?

300
00:15:45,041 --> 00:15:46,625
-[FREE] She stole it!
-[gasps]

301
00:15:48,666 --> 00:15:50,958
[MARLYA panting]

302
00:15:58,375 --> 00:15:59,791
Think you’ll be able
to keep up?

303
00:15:59,875 --> 00:16:02,291
-Yes, sir.
-Stay close.

304
00:16:02,375 --> 00:16:05,583
♪

305
00:16:21,125 --> 00:16:23,458
This church hasn’t been
in use for years.

306
00:16:30,250 --> 00:16:31,375
What’s down there?

307
00:16:31,458 --> 00:16:33,458
A network of endless tunnels.

308
00:16:33,541 --> 00:16:34,666
There’s a maze of old water

309
00:16:34,750 --> 00:16:37,666
and sewer passageways
beneath Isharat.

310
00:16:37,750 --> 00:16:39,541
Crypts as well,
if I remember right.

311
00:16:40,750 --> 00:16:42,833
Oh, great.

312
00:16:53,208 --> 00:16:55,208
I think someone’s living here.

313
00:16:55,291 --> 00:16:56,583
[FREE]
Looks like it.

314
00:17:17,708 --> 00:17:19,625
[MARLYA]
A person!

315
00:17:19,708 --> 00:17:21,250
Formerly.

316
00:17:24,333 --> 00:17:26,041
[MARLYA whimpers]

317
00:17:26,125 --> 00:17:27,541
-[gun clicks]
-[FREE inhales sharply]

318
00:17:27,625 --> 00:17:29,750
-[MARLYA gasps]
-[gunfire]

319
00:17:36,125 --> 00:17:37,333
Get inside of there!

320
00:17:37,416 --> 00:17:38,541
[MARLYA]
With him?

321
00:17:38,625 --> 00:17:40,458
Do it, or you’ll both be dead!

322
00:17:44,666 --> 00:17:46,416
Howl, Red Hood!

323
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:48,666
[roaring]

324
00:17:48,750 --> 00:17:50,125
[explosion]

325
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,541
[MARLYA]
I can’t see anything!

326
00:17:53,625 --> 00:17:56,166
Yeah, and neither can they.
Just stay put.

327
00:17:56,250 --> 00:17:57,708
[RED HOWL snarls]

328
00:17:59,541 --> 00:18:01,500
[FREE]
You want me to follow you.

329
00:18:01,583 --> 00:18:02,916
What for?

330
00:18:15,375 --> 00:18:17,250
What’re they after?

331
00:18:17,333 --> 00:18:20,791
Doesn’t matter if they’re
with Arcame or Gui Carlin.

332
00:18:20,875 --> 00:18:23,458
If they were only after
the Black Fairy Tome,

333
00:18:23,541 --> 00:18:25,833
they could’ve gotten away.

334
00:18:25,916 --> 00:18:27,416
Are they after me?

335
00:18:29,166 --> 00:18:31,458
[FREE]
Get off him!

336
00:18:31,541 --> 00:18:33,875
[PATTY screaming]

337
00:18:36,208 --> 00:18:37,250
[PATTY grunts]

338
00:18:38,916 --> 00:18:39,958
[screams]

339
00:18:40,041 --> 00:18:41,208
Just who is this bitch?

340
00:18:41,291 --> 00:18:44,416
-[objects crashing]
-[PATTY grunting]

341
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:45,916
[MARLYA]
I’m unlucky.

342
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,666
I’m convinced of it.

343
00:18:50,291 --> 00:18:51,791
-[bones clatter]
-[MARLYA gasps]

344
00:18:51,875 --> 00:18:53,166
Forgive me.

345
00:18:54,958 --> 00:18:57,291
[MARLYA]
I’ve been a little disaster.

346
00:18:57,375 --> 00:18:59,166
Since the day I was born.

347
00:19:01,791 --> 00:19:03,041
[MARLYA gasps]

348
00:19:03,125 --> 00:19:05,833
It was pitch black
only a second ago.

349
00:19:05,916 --> 00:19:08,041
So, who?

350
00:19:08,125 --> 00:19:10,583
-[gunshot]
-[rifle cocks]

351
00:19:12,375 --> 00:19:14,166
[MAN]
Where do you think you’re going?

352
00:19:14,250 --> 00:19:15,833
[gunshot]

353
00:19:17,916 --> 00:19:19,125
[rifle cocks]

354
00:19:19,208 --> 00:19:23,083
[breathing heavily]

355
00:19:23,166 --> 00:19:25,458
[MARLYA]
I used to envy Ver.

356
00:19:25,541 --> 00:19:28,500
She was constantly
surrounded by people.

357
00:19:28,583 --> 00:19:31,458
Always laughing and radiant.

358
00:19:31,541 --> 00:19:33,083
She had friends.

359
00:19:33,166 --> 00:19:35,208
A family that was
actually related to her.

360
00:19:35,291 --> 00:19:36,791
[MAN, echoing]
Patty was clear.

361
00:19:36,875 --> 00:19:38,083
I’m to capture you.

362
00:19:38,166 --> 00:19:40,916
Seems she means
to use you as bait

363
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:44,458
should Free Underbar
prove too formidable.

364
00:19:44,541 --> 00:19:47,125
You might not be able to tell
upon first meeting her,

365
00:19:47,208 --> 00:19:48,625
but she is quite cautious.

366
00:19:48,708 --> 00:19:50,458
You’re behind me,
aren’t you?

367
00:19:52,041 --> 00:19:53,208
-[MAN grunts]
-[metal scraping]

368
00:19:54,833 --> 00:19:56,458
The more you keep resisting,

369
00:19:56,541 --> 00:19:58,583
the more beautiful
my work will be.

370
00:19:58,666 --> 00:20:00,750
I have a suspicion
you’ll wind up

371
00:20:00,833 --> 00:20:03,458
being one of my
finest masterpieces.

372
00:20:03,541 --> 00:20:04,583
Lady.

373
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:07,875
[MARLYA]
What the hell’s going on?

374
00:20:09,375 --> 00:20:11,375
[panting]

375
00:20:11,458 --> 00:20:14,041
[eerie chuckling]

376
00:20:15,750 --> 00:20:18,666
The name’s Jonathan,
and I’m a true artist!

377
00:20:18,750 --> 00:20:20,500
-[metal pinging]
-[MARLYA yelps]

378
00:20:20,583 --> 00:20:22,333
Oh, but whatever you do,

379
00:20:22,416 --> 00:20:24,250
don’t refer to me
as “Jon.”

380
00:20:24,333 --> 00:20:26,541
I want you to call me
Jonathan,

381
00:20:26,625 --> 00:20:28,791
or Jona if you prefer.

382
00:20:34,250 --> 00:20:35,875
[grunts]

383
00:20:35,958 --> 00:20:39,750
♪

384
00:20:41,333 --> 00:20:43,041
[MARLYA]
I’m through running!

385
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:46,583
-[JONATHAN grunts]
-[MARLYA yelps]

386
00:20:48,750 --> 00:20:50,875
[gunshot]

387
00:20:50,958 --> 00:20:53,833
Don’t you realize,
pain is a blessing, lady?

388
00:20:54,958 --> 00:20:56,666
[screams]

389
00:20:59,875 --> 00:21:02,250
I have to hurt you.
The more I do,

390
00:21:02,333 --> 00:21:04,958
the closer it brings me
to the truth!

391
00:21:09,708 --> 00:21:11,250
[MARLYA]
This guy’s insane.

392
00:21:11,333 --> 00:21:13,750
Nothing he’s says
makes any sense.

393
00:21:16,083 --> 00:21:17,166
My fairy.

394
00:21:17,250 --> 00:21:18,666
I still can’t summon it!

395
00:21:18,750 --> 00:21:21,791
Let me clarify
what I mean by “art”.

396
00:21:21,875 --> 00:21:24,375
It’s the act of understanding
another person!

397
00:21:24,458 --> 00:21:26,541
[gun clattering]

398
00:21:26,625 --> 00:21:28,500
[MARLYA groans]

399
00:21:28,583 --> 00:21:30,250
[JONATHAN]
I want to be someone

400
00:21:30,333 --> 00:21:32,250
who understands you
inside and out.

401
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:34,208
[glass shattering]

402
00:21:43,583 --> 00:21:45,041
-[glass shatters]
-[JONATHAN gasps]

403
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:51,875
[MARLYA gasps]
Ver!

404
00:21:51,958 --> 00:21:54,125
[YOUNG MARLYA crying]

405
00:21:54,208 --> 00:21:57,875
Everything’s alright.
Don’t cry, Marlya.

406
00:21:59,208 --> 00:22:00,375
[MARLYA gasps]

407
00:22:00,458 --> 00:22:02,166
[metal scrapes]

408
00:22:04,708 --> 00:22:07,916
[YOUNG VERONICA] Trust me.
I won’t let anything bad happen.

409
00:23:38,416 --> 00:23:40,041
[MARLYA] Ver!

410
00:23:40,125 --> 00:23:42,666
Am I a little disaster
like everyone says?

411
00:23:42,750 --> 00:23:44,791
[VERONICA]
Because I’m still empty inside.

412
00:23:44,875 --> 00:23:47,791
It’s your fault, all of it!
Ray Dawn!

